text: Butternut squash (Cucurbita moschata), sometimes known in Australia and New Zealand as butternut pumpkin or gramma, is a type of winter squash that grows on a vine. It has a sweet, nutty taste similar to that of a pumpkin. It has tan-yellow skin and orange fleshy pulp with a compartment of seeds in the blossom end. == References == Category:Cucurbitaceae Category:Fruits Category:Vegetables Category:Thanksgiving
title: Butternut squash
